pple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/280","type":"link","title":"Cook up a rich text experience in SwiftUI with AttributedString","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/280","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cook up a rich text experience in SwiftUI with AttributedString"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps":{"title":"What’s new in Metal rendering for immersive apps","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the latest improvements in Metal rendering for immersive apps with Compositor Services. Learn how to add hover effects to highlight your app’s interactive elements, and how to render in higher fidelity with dynamic render quality. Find out about the new progressive immersion style. And explore how you can bring immersive experiences to macOS apps by directly rendering Metal content from Mac to Vision Pro."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-294-whats-new-in-metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/256":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/256","type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/256"},"https://philz.work":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/philz.work","title":"Blog","identifier":"https:\/\/philz.work"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/238":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/238","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Customize your app for Assistive Access"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/238","title":"Customize your app for Assistive Access"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/323":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/323","type":"link","title":"Build a SwiftUI app with the new design","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/323","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Build a SwiftUI app with the new design","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/tab/init(role:content:)":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"code":"role","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/tab\/init(role:content:)","title":"the role initializer","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/tab\/init(role:content:)"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/306":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/306","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optimize SwiftUI performance with Instruments"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/306","title":"Optimize SwiftUI performance with Instruments"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-306-Optimize-SwiftUI-performance-with-Instruments":{"title":"Optimize SwiftUI performance with Instruments","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-306-optimize-swiftui-performance-with-instruments","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the new SwiftUI instrument. We’ll cover how SwiftUI updates views, how changes in your app’s data affect those updates, and how the new instrument helps you visualize those causes and effects."}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-306-Optimize-SwiftUI-performance-with-Instruments"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-290-Set-the-scene-with-SwiftUI-in-visionOS":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-290-Set-the-scene-with-SwiftUI-in-visionOS","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-290-set-the-scene-with-swiftui-in-visionos","abstract":[{"text":"Discover exciting new APIs to enhance windows, volumes, and immersive spaces in your visionOS app. Fine tune the behavior of your scenes when relaunched or locked in place. Make volumes adapt to their surroundings with clipping margins and snapping. Stream immersive content from Mac to Vision Pro. Elevate your existing UIKit-based apps with volumes and immersive spaces.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Set the scene with SwiftUI in visionOS"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/225":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/225","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Explore localization with Xcode"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/225","title":"Explore localization with Xcode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-268-Embracing-Swift-concurrency":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-268-embracing-swift-concurrency","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-268-Embracing-Swift-concurrency","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Join us to learn the core Swift concurrency concepts. Concurrency helps you improve app responsiveness and performance, and Swift is designed to make asynchronous and concurrent code easier to write correctly. We’ll cover the steps you need to take an app through from single-threaded to concurrent. We’ll also help you determine how and when to make the best use of Swift concurrency features – whether it’s making your code more asynchronous, moving it to the background, or sharing data across concurrent tasks."}],"title":"Embracing Swift concurrency"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-274-Better-together-SwiftUI-and-RealityKit":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-274-better-together-swiftui-and-realitykit","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover how to seamlessly blend SwiftUI and RealityKit in visionOS 26. We’ll explore enhancements to Model3D, including animation and ConfigurationCatalog support, and demonstrate smooth transitions to RealityView. You’ll learn how to leverage SwiftUI animations to drive RealityKit component changes, implement interactive manipulation, use new SwiftUI components for richer interactions, and observe RealityKit changes from your SwiftUI code. We’ll also cover how to use unified coordinate conversion for cross-framework coordinate transformations."}],"title":"Better together: SwiftUI and RealityKit","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-274-Better-together-SwiftUI-and-RealityKit","role":"sampleCode"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/dragpreviewsformation(_:)":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragpreviewsformation(_:)","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragpreviewsformation(_:)","title":"dragPreviewsFormation","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"dragPreviewsFormation","type":"codeVoice"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/294":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/294","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What’s new in Metal rendering for immersive apps"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/294","title":"What’s new in Metal rendering for immersive apps"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-273-Meet-SwiftUI-spatial-layout":{"title":"Meet SwiftUI spatial layout","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Explore new tools for building spatial experiences using SwiftUI. Learn the basics of 3D SwiftUI views on visionOS, customize existing layouts with depth alignments, and use modifiers to rotate and position views in space. Discover how to use spatial containers to align views in the same 3D space, helping you create immersive and engaging apps.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-273-meet-swiftui-spatial-layout","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-273-Meet-SwiftUI-spatial-layout","kind":"article"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/208":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/208","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Elevate the design of your iPad app"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/208","title":"Elevate the design of your iPad app"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/nsgesturerecognizerrepresentable":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/nsgesturerecognizerrepresentable","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/nsgesturerecognizerrepresentable","title":"NSGestureRecognizerRepresentable","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"NSGestureRecognizerRepresentable","type":"codeVoice"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/philptr":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/philptr","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"macOS UI, Frameworks, and Systems. Previously AppKit @ Apple","type":"text"}],"title":"Phil Zakharchenko (7 notes)","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"philptr.jpeg"},{"type":"icon","identifier":"philptr.jpeg"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/philptr","role":"sampleCode"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"image","alt":null},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/274":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/274","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Better together: SwiftUI and RealityKit"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/274","title":"Better together: SwiftUI and RealityKit"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-317-Whats-new-in-visionOS-26":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-317-Whats-new-in-visionOS-26","kind":"article","title":"What’s new in visionOS 26","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Explore exciting new features in visionOS 26. Discover enhanced volumetric APIs and learn how you can combine the power of SwiftUI, RealityKit and ARKit. Find out how you can build more engaging apps and games using faster hand tracking and input from spatial accessories. Get a sneak peek at updates to SharePlay, Compositor Services, immersive media, spatial web, Enterprise APIs, and much more."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-317-whats-new-in-visionos-26","role":"sampleCode"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/278":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/278","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What’s new in widgets"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/278","title":"What’s new in widgets"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-238-Customize-your-app-for-Assistive-Access":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-238-Customize-your-app-for-Assistive-Access","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-238-customize-your-app-for-assistive-access","abstract":[{"text":"Assistive Access is a distinctive, focused iOS experience that makes it easier for people with cognitive disabilities to use iPhone and iPad independently. In iOS and iPadOS 26, you can customize your app when it’s running in Assistive Access to give people greater ease and independence. Learn how to tailor your app using the AssistiveAccess SwiftUI scene type, and explore the key design principles that can help you create a high-quality Assistive Access experience for everyone.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Customize your app for Assistive Access"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributions are welcome!"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Contributions are welcome!"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/glasseffect(_:in:isenabled:)":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/glasseffect(_:in:isenabled:)","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/glasseffect(_:in:isenabled:)","title":"glassEffect","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"glassEffect","type":"codeVoice"}]},"WWDC25-256-3D-Charts":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-256-3D-Charts.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-256-3D-Charts","type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-225-Codealong-Explore-localization-with-Xcode":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-225-Codealong-Explore-localization-with-Xcode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-225-codealong-explore-localization-with-xcode","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to localize your app into additional languages using Xcode. We’ll walk step-by-step through the process of creating a String Catalog, translating text, and exchanging files with external translators. You’ll learn best practices for providing necessary context to translators and how Xcode can help to provide this information automatically. For larger projects, we’ll also dive into techniques to manage complexity and streamline string management using type-safe Swift code.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Code-along: Explore localization with Xcode"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/windowresizeanchor(_:)":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/windowresizeanchor(_:)","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"windowResizeAnchor"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/windowresizeanchor(_:)","title":"windowResizeAnchor"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-208-Elevate-the-design-of-your-iPad-app":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Elevate the design of your iPad app","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-208-elevate-the-design-of-your-ipad-app","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-208-Elevate-the-design-of-your-iPad-app","abstract":[{"text":"Make your app look and feel great on iPadOS. Learn best practices for designing a responsive layout for resizable app windows. Get familiar with window controls and explore the best ways to accommodate them. Discover the building blocks of a great menu bar. And meet the new pointer and its updated effects.","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/dragconfiguration(_:)":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragconfiguration(_:)","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragconfiguration(_:)","title":"dragConfiguration","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"dragConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/dragcontainer(for:id:in:_:)":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragcontainer(for:id:in:_:)","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dragContainer"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/dragcontainer(for:id:in:_:)","title":"dragContainer"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-266-Explore-concurrency-in-SwiftUI":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Explore concurrency in SwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-266-explore-concurrency-in-swiftui","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-266-Explore-concurrency-in-SwiftUI","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how SwiftUI leverages Swift concurrency to build safe and responsive apps. Explore how SwiftUI uses the main actor by default and offloads work to other actors. Learn how to interpret concurrency annotations and manage async tasks with SwiftUI’s event loop for smooth animations and UI updates. You’ll leave knowing how to avoid data races and write code fearlessly.","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/spatialoverlay(alignment:content:)":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/spatialoverlay(alignment:content:)","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spatialOverlay"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/spatialoverlay(alignment:content:)","title":"spatialOverlay"},"philptr":{"type":"image","identifier":"philptr","alt":"Profile image of Phil Zakharchenko","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/philptr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-280-Codealong-Cook-up-a-rich-text-experience-in-SwiftUI-with-AttributedString":{"title":"Code-along: Cook up a rich text experience in SwiftUI with AttributedString","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-280-Codealong-Cook-up-a-rich-text-experience-in-SwiftUI-with-AttributedString","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-280-codealong-cook-up-a-rich-text-experience-in-swiftui-with-attributedstring","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to build a rich text experience with SwiftUI’s TextEditor API and AttributedString. Discover how you can enable rich text editing, build custom controls that manipulate the contents of your editor, and customize the formatting options available. Explore advanced capabilities of AttributedString that help you craft the best text editing experiences.","type":"text"}]}}}